<subSubSection lastPageId="54" lastPageNumber="145" pageId="53" pageNumber="144" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="53.[136,1452,1824,2092]" pageId="53" pageNumber="144">
Diagnosis. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yaginuma, 1960" authorityName="Yaginuma" authorityYear="1960" box="[637,933,1824,1848]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Episinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="53" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nubilus">
<emphasis box="[637,747,1824,1848]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="144">E. nubilus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yaginuma" box="[754,933,1824,1848]" pageId="53" pageNumber="144" refId="ref20682" refString="Yaginuma, T. 1960. Spiders of Japan in Colour. Hoikusha Osaka, 186 pp." type="book" year="1960">Yaginuma, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be distinguished by the Sp, which is straight in ventral view; the C surrounds the tip of the E and is hooked distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="53.[136,1452,1824,2092]" lastBlockId="54.[136,1452,236,746]" lastPageId="54" lastPageNumber="145" pageId="53" pageNumber="144">
Description. Male (
<typeStatus box="[396,494,1894,1918]" pageId="53" pageNumber="144">holotype</typeStatus>
, IZCAS-Ar42461, 
<figureCitation box="[698,831,1894,1918]" captionStart="Figure 44" captionStartId="50.[155,218,2026,2048]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,764,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-304@50.[189,1399,764,1979]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Figure 44. Episinus tongyani Lin &amp; Li, sp. nov., holotype male, left palp. A. Prolateral view; B. Ventral view; C. Retrolateral view. Scale bars=0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367151/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="144">Figs 44A–C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[841,921,1894,1918]" captionStart="Figure 46" captionStartId="52.[155,218,2008,2030]" captionText="Figure 46. Episinus tongyani Lin &amp; Li, sp. nov., paratype female and holotype male.A. Vulva, dorsal view; B. Epigyne, ventral view; C. Left palp, ventral view; D. Left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars=0.1mm." pageId="53" pageNumber="144">46C–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[932,978,1894,1918]" captionStart="Figure 53" captionStartId="59.[155,218,1963,1985]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,577,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-242@59.[189,1399,577,1917]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="Figure 53. Habitus of six new Theridiidae species, male dorsal view (A–C, E, G–L), lateral view (H, J, L) and female dorsal view (B, D, F, H). A–B. Episinus bonjovi Lin &amp; Li, sp. nov.; C–D, E. jiangweni Lin &amp; Li, sp. nov.; E–F. E. tongyani Lin &amp; Li, sp. nov.; G–H. Meotipa luoqiae Lin &amp; Li, sp. nov.; I–J. M. menglun Lin &amp; Li, sp. nov.; K–L. M. zhengguoi Lin &amp; Li, sp. nov. Scale bars= 1.0mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367163/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="144">53E</figureCitation>
). Total length 2.50. Prosoma 0.81 long, 0.73 wide, flat, pale yellow, anterior part of ocular area with two distinct processes. Sternum 0.53 long, 0.44 wide, pale yellow. Opisthosoma 1.28 long, 1.38 wide, pale yellow with large white spots in dorsal view. Eyes developed: AME 0.13, ALE 0.08, PME 0.09, PLE 0.08, AME–AME 0.08, AME–ALE 0.05, PME–PME 0.05, PME–PLE 0.03. Clypeus height about same size as AME diameter. Leg I femur 2.00, patella 0.40, tibia 1.75, metatarsus 2.13, tarsus 0.75. Patella and tibia II–IV: 1.65, 0.65, 1.30. Legs yellow to black, femur and tibia with a line of dorsal bristles; metatarsus with a line of bristles in dorsal and ventral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[136,1452,236,746]" box="[189,1437,271,295]" pageId="54" pageNumber="145">
Palp (
<figureCitation box="[251,385,271,295]" captionStart="Figure 44" captionStartId="50.[155,218,2026,2048]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,764,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-304@50.[189,1399,764,1979]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Figure 44. Episinus tongyani Lin &amp; Li, sp. nov., holotype male, left palp. A. Prolateral view; B. Ventral view; C. Retrolateral view. Scale bars=0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367151/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="145">Figs 44A–C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[395,474,271,295]" captionStart="Figure 46" captionStartId="52.[155,218,2008,2030]" captionText="Figure 46. Episinus tongyani Lin &amp; Li, sp. nov., paratype female and holotype male.A. Vulva, dorsal view; B. Epigyne, ventral view; C. Left palp, ventral view; D. Left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars=0.1mm." pageId="54" pageNumber="145">46C–D</figureCitation>
) tibia long; Sp straight in ventral view; E long, slender; C large, surrounding the end of E.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[136,1452,236,746]" pageId="54" pageNumber="145">
Female (
<typeStatus box="[281,377,306,330]" pageId="54" pageNumber="145">paratype</typeStatus>
, IZCAS-Ar42465, 45A–B, 46A–B, 53F). Total length 3.00–3.50. Prosoma 1.00–1.13 long, 1.00–1.05 wide, flat, pale yellow, anterior part of ocular area with two distinct processes. Sternum 0.63–0.68 long, 0.55–0.62 wide, pale yellow. Opisthosoma 1.88–2.00 long, 2.63–3.13 wide, yellow, with white spots. Eyes developed. Legs similar to those of male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[136,1452,236,746]" pageId="54" pageNumber="145">
Epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[314,446,444,468]" captionStart="Figure 45" captionStartId="51.[155,218,2034,2056]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,273,1988]" captionTargetId="figure-31@51.[189,1399,273,1989]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="Figure 45. Episinus tongyani Lin &amp; Li, sp. nov., paratype female. A. Epigyne, ventral view; B. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367153" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367153/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="145">Figs 45A–B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[456,535,444,468]" captionStart="Figure 46" captionStartId="52.[155,218,2008,2030]" captionText="Figure 46. Episinus tongyani Lin &amp; Li, sp. nov., paratype female and holotype male.A. Vulva, dorsal view; B. Epigyne, ventral view; C. Left palp, ventral view; D. Left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars=0.1mm." pageId="54" pageNumber="145">46A–B</figureCitation>
) flat; S curved; CD long, winding, opening to the anterior margin of atrium; FDs short, falcate.
</paragraph>
